§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ An ❬orthogonal matrix❭ is a matrix $U ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$ whose
    columns are orthonormal. ⦉

  ‖ Since an orthogonal matrix has $n$ columns, its columns are
    a basis for $𝗥^n$. ⦉
